[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Fuzzing context  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  The bug was triggered by the `json_fuzz` harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`src/json_fuzz.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, which calls[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minto `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`. The fuzzer loads a single testcase, then invokes the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparser with `json_parse` → `json_parse_ex`. LibFuzzer’s entropic power schedule and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAddressSanitizer instrumentation report the overflow during a repeated run [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m100[0m[39m [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39miterations[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m of the same input.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Vulnerable code location  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  The overflow occurs at:[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    • `json_parse_ex` in `src/shadowsocks/src/json.c`, line [0m[1;36m620[0m[39m, column [0m[1;36m29[0m[39m.  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    • Called by `json_parse` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m958[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    • Ultimately invoked from the fuzz target at `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` in [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`json_fuzz.[0m[1;92mc:12[0m[39m`.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Observations and findings  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The allocation in question is only [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m bytes long, and the code reads one more [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbyte at offset [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39maddress [0m[1;36m0x5020000000b5[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, crossing the heap left redzone.  [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • ASan’s shadow memory shows the byte at that address is in a redzone [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`fa`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconfirming an out-of-bounds read.  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The stack trace pins the overflow to parsing logic, not the harness itself.  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The fuzzer run uses environment variables [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[33mRUN_FUZZER_MODE[0m[39m=[0m[35minteractive[0m[39m`, [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[33mFUZZING_ENGINE[0m[39m=[0m[35mlibfuzzer[0m[39m`, `[0m[33mSKIP_SEED_CORPUS[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and runs with `-[0m[33mrss_limit_mb[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m2560[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-[0m[33mtimeout[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m25[0m[39m`.[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Code areas for investigation  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  To fully understand the extent of this issue, review:[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. The byte‐level parsing loops and buffer boundary checks in `json_parse_ex`. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. How input length is determined and how buffers are allocated and accessed in[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`json_parse`.  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. The fuzz target in `json_fuzz.c` for how inputs are passed into the parser [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39me.g., reading from `[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. Any helper or utility functions used by `json_parse_ex` for advancing [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpointers or peeking ahead in the input buffer.[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mNo speculation on root causes or fixes is included; the purpose of this report is [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto outline the issue’s nature, its location, and related code areas for a [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcomprehensive review.[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Original code tested `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mend - state.ptr < [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m || …[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, intending to ensure four[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhex digits remain.  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Patch changed it to:[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       ```[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[35m/[0m[39m* need at least [0m[32m'u'[0m[39m plus four hex digits *[0m[35m/[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mend - state.ptr < [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m ||[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[1;39m([0m[39muc_b1 = [0m[1;35mhex_value[0m[1;39m([0m[39m*++state.ptr[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m == [0m[1;36m0xFF[0m[39m ||[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           …[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[1;39m([0m[39muc_b4 = [0m[1;35mhex_value[0m[1;39m([0m[39m*++state.ptr[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m == [0m[1;36m0xFF[0m[1;39m)[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[1;35msprintf[0m[1;39m([0m[39merror, …[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           goto e_failed;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       ```[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This adjustment is intended to account for the ‘u’ character itself plus the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfour digits.[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Post-Patch Result  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A fresh run of the same fuzzer command reproduces an AddressSanitizer [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheap-buffer-overflow at json.[0m[1;92mc:621[0m[39m—immediately after the adjusted check line.  [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The error remains a [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m-byte read just beyond a [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m-byte allocation, indicating [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe bounds check is still insufficient or misplaced.  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The stack trace and shadow bytes are nearly identical to the pre-patch [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfailure, confirming no change in behavior.[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The logic around `state.ptr` arithmetic and the exact definition of [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`end`—verify whether `end` points to the last valid byte or one past the buffer.  [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The sequencing of `*++state.ptr` increments: ensure that pointer advances and [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecks do not outpace buffer bounds.  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - How hex digits are consumed and validated: consider whether combining pointer [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmovement and validation in a single expression could skip or mis-evaluate boundary [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconditions.  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overall flow in `json_parse_ex` for string literals and escape sequences, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto catch any additional off-by-one risks or redzone violations.  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Any interactions with `string_add` or error-handling paths that may conceal [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe true buffer limits at parse time.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  Container overflow:      fc[0m                                                       [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  Right alloca redzone:    cb[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m==[0m[1;36m18[0m[39m==ABORTING[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msubprocess command returned a non-zero exit status: [0m[1;36m1[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mINFO:__main__:Running: docker run --privileged --shm-[0m[33msize[0m[39m=[0m[35m2g[0m[39m --platform linux/amd64[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m--rm -i -e [0m[33mHELPER[0m[39m=[0m[3;92mTrue[0m[39m -e [0m[33mARCHITECTURE[0m[39m=[0m[35mx86_64[0m[39m -v [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/home/qqor/aixcc/crete/packages/python_oss_fuzz/.oss_fuzz/build/out/[0m[95mshadowsocks[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mou[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [95mt[0m[39m -v [0m[35m/tmp/[0m[95mtmpbqa7bra0[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m -t ghcr.io/aixcc-finals/base-runner:v1.[0m[1;36m3.0[0m[39m [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreproduce json_fuzz -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fuzzer `json_fuzz` discovered a heap-buffer-overflow in `json_parse_ex` [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39msrc/shadowsocks/src/json.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m when handling short or malformed `\uXXXX` escapes. A [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mproposed patch rewrote the Unicode‐escape parsing logic to:[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Use a temporary pointer [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`p`, `p2`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to validate that at least five or seven [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcharacters remain before decoding.[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Check each hex digit without advancing the main parser pointer.[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Only advance `state.ptr` after validating the sequence.[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Decode both single escapes and surrogate pairs in a guarded fashion.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter applying the patch, the code fails to compile with nine errors:  [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Discarding `const` qualifiers when assigning `state.ptr` to `char *`.  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. `sprintf` calls having mismatched format specifiers and extra arguments due to [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe `line_and_col` macro.  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Uninitialized use of `uc_b3` and `uc_b4` in one of the branches.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Under fuzzing, `json_parse_ex` reads one byte past the end of an allocated [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m-byte buffer when encountering a `\u` escape at the very end of the input.  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - AddressSanitizer reports a heap-buffer-overflow at `json.[0m[1;92mc:620:29[0m[39m`, with the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcall stack rooted in `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`.  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The region `[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mptr, ptr+[0m[1;36m5[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` exists but the code performs `*++state.ptr` up to [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfour times without confirming there are enough bytes left, leading to OOB reads.[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Important Observations  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer run shows `end - state.ptr` checks that use a “< [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m” comparison but [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdo not fully guard against minimal input lengths when combined with pointer [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mincrements.  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The macro `line_and_col` expands to two arguments [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`state.cur_line, [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstate.cur_col`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, which must match format specifiers.  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `state.ptr` is declared as `const char *`, so any temporary pointer to it [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mshould also be `const char *`.  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Variables `uc_b1, uc_b2, uc_b3, uc_b4` are declared together but in the new [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlogic some branches no longer initialize all of them before use.[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Replaces the original four‐digit hex decode with a branch that:[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     * Saves `state.ptr` into `char *p`.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     * Checks `end - p < [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m` before reading `p+[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m`…`p+[0m[1;36m4[0m[39m`.[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     * Parses hex digits into `h1`…`h4` and bails out on invalid values.[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     * Advances `state.ptr = p + [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m` before assembling `uchar`.[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Adds a guarded surrogate‐pair branch:[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     * Saves `state.ptr` into `char *p2`.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     * Checks `end - p2 < [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m`, verifies the literal `[0m[32m"\u"[0m[39m` at `p2+[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m`…`p2+[0m[1;36m2[0m[39m`.[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     * Parses `l1`…`l4` from `p2+[0m[1;36m3[0m[39m`…`p2+[0m[1;36m6[0m[39m` and advances `state.ptr = p2 + [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m`.[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     * Combines high and low surrogates into a single code point.[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Patch Result [0m[1;39m([0m[39mCompiler Errors[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Two instances of “initializing ‘char *’ with an expression of type ‘const char[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m*’” at lines assigning `p` and `p2`.  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Four format‐string warnings where `[0m[1;35msprintf[0m[1;39m([0m[39merror, [0m[32m"... %d:%d"[0m[39m, line_and_col[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpasses two ints but the literal has only one “%d:%d” placeholder or vice versa.  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Two uninitialized‐variable errors for `uc_b3` and `uc_b4` when they are later [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mused in the fallback assembly logic.[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The declaration of `state.ptr`: adjust temporary pointers to `const char *` or[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcast appropriately.  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The definition of the `line_and_col` macro: ensure it aligns with each [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`sprintf` format string.  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The initialization and usage of `uc_b1`…`uc_b4`: review all code paths to [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mguarantee they are set before any arithmetic combines them.  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Surrounding logic in `json_parse_ex` to confirm all boundary checks [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconsistently prevent over‐reads for other escape sequences.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fuzzer run against `json_fuzz` uncovered a heap-buffer-overflow in [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`json_parse_ex` [0m[1;39m([0m[39msrc/json.[0m[1;92mc:620[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m when handling `\u` escapes. An attempted patch [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrewrote the Unicode‐escape handling logic—replacing the original inline decoding [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith a more structured parse of code units and surrogate pairs, followed by [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexplicit UTF-[0m[1;36m8[0m[39m emission. However, applying the patch yielded numerous compile [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39merrors [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g. “`default` statement not in switch statement”, “use of undeclared [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39midentifier [0m[32m'b'[0m[39m”[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, indicating misplacement of braces or removal of context around [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe switch covering character escapes.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- A one‐byte read past the end of a [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m‐byte heap allocation was detected by [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAddressSanitizer during fuzzing.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The failure stack trace shows the overflow occurred in `json_parse_ex` while [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprocessing a `\uXXXX` escape inside a JSON string.[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The specific read happens immediately after the allocated region for the escape [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msequence, suggesting insufficient bounds checks before interpreting hex digits or [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39madvancing the parser pointer.[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mImportant Observations[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The overflow triggers when the code advances `state.ptr` beyond the buffer end [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand then reads a hex digit.[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The dump reports `end - state.ptr < [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m` as a check, but pointer increments inside [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe case block can walk past the limit.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The allocated buffer for the input is only five bytes long; the code assumes at [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mleast four hex characters following `\u`.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The bug surfaces deterministically under a single test input run [0m[1;36m100[0m[39m times, [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindicating stable reproduction.[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The patch removes the original fall‐through of `case [0m[32m'u'[0m[39m:` and replaces it with:[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - A local pointer `p` to validate there are at least five characters [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[32m"\u"[0m[39m` + [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhex digits[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Calls to `[0m[1;35mhex_value[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` for each digit, with explicit checks against `[0m[1;36m0xFF[0m[39m`.[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Pointer adjustments [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`state.ptr = p + [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to move past the parsed digits.[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Handling of surrogate pairs by looking for `[0m[32m"\u"[0m[39m` again, validating [0m[1;36m7[0m[39m more [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbytes, and computing the full code point.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Emitting UTF-[0m[1;36m8[0m[39m bytes via `[0m[1;35mstring_add[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` branches based on the code value.[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- After the patch, compilation produces ~[0m[1;36m20[0m[39m errors, the first being:[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    json.[0m[1;92mc:395:19[0m[39m: error: [0m[32m'default'[0m[39m statement not in switch statement[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Subsequent errors cite undeclared identifier `b` at many locations, showing that [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe patch disrupted the surrounding parsing logic—likely due to mismatched braces [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mor removal of the `[0m[1;35mswitch[0m[1;39m([0m[39mb = *state.ptr[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` context.[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The errors continue through comment parsing sections and other switch/case [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconstructs, indicating that the patch inserted or deleted lines affecting a large [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mswitch statement block.[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mParts for Further Investigation[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Escape Parsing Switch**  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The `switch` in `json_parse_ex` that dispatches on the escape character [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g.,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`case [0m[32m'\\'`, `case '[0m[39m"[0m[32m'`, `case '[0m[39mu'`, `default`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Ensure braces around `case [0m[32m'u'[0m[39m: [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m … [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m break;` remain balanced and that the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`default:` label is still inside the same `switch`.[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **`state.ptr` and Bounds Checks**  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The logic computing `end - state.ptr` and subsequent pointer increments.[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Confirm that each pointer advance is guarded by a comparison against `end`.[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **`[0m[1;35mhex_value[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` Semantics**  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Validate that `hex_value` consistently returns `[0m[1;36m0xFF[0m[39m` on invalid input and [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnever consumes input beyond buffer.[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **UTF-[0m[1;36m8[0m[39m Emission via `[0m[1;35mstring_add[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`**  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The expected behavior of `string_add` regarding buffer growth or reallocation.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Whether multi-byte emission properly accounts for `state.first_pass` mode.[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Surrounding Parser Context**  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overall structure of `json_parse_ex`, including comment parsing, [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhitespace handling, and other escapes.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Ensuring the patch did not misplace any labels or affect neighboring logic.[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fuzzer discovered a heap-buffer-overflow in `json_parse_ex` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mjson.[0m[1;92mc:620[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m when [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhandling certain inputs. A patch attempt rewrote the Unicode-escape parsing [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mblock—replacing the original byte-by-byte logic with a two-pass pointer-based [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mapproach—but after applying it the build fails with several “unused variable” [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39merrors [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`uchar`, `uc_b1`, `uc_b2`, `uc_b3`, `uc_b4`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in json.c. No further errors [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mare shown beyond these compiler complaints.[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - During fuzzing of the JSON parser [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`json_fuzz`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, AddressSanitizer reports a [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mone-byte read past a [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m-byte heap allocation in `json_parse_ex` at json.[0m[1;92mc:620[0m[39m.  [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The crash stack shows the overflow originates in the code path that decodes [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`\uXXXX` or surrogate-pair escapes.  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m-byte region corresponds to the minimal size of the fuzzed input buffer [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msupplied for testing.  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Important Observations  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overflow happens on a read immediately after the allocated buffer end [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;36m0x5020000000b5[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The error is scoped to the Unicode-escape handling logic in `json_parse_ex`.  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The original code manually incremented `state.ptr` and decoded hex nibble by [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnibble, handling both single code units and surrogate pairs.  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The patch completely replaced the existing `case [0m[32m'u'[0m[39m:` block [0m[1;39m([0m[39mstarting around [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mline [0m[1;36m302[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m with a new pointer-based parsing sequence.  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - New logic introduces local pointers `p` and `q` to verify sufficient remaining[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlength before accessing each escape sequence.  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The code unconditionally declares five byte-sized variables [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`uchar`, `uc_b1`,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`uc_b2`, `uc_b3`, `uc_b4`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m at function scope, but the new logic never refers to [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthem; instead it uses local `d1..d4`, `e1..e4`, and `code`.  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - After applying the patch, the compiler emits errors for the five unused [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvariables, and due to `-Werror` these stop the build.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Patch Result  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Compiler errors in json.c:  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     json.[0m[1;92mc:269:18[0m[39m: error: unused variable ‘uchar’  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     json.[0m[1;92mc:270:21[0m[39m: error: unused variable ‘uc_b1’  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     json.[0m[1;92mc:270:28[0m[39m: error: unused variable ‘uc_b2’  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     json.[0m[1;92mc:270:35[0m[39m: error: unused variable ‘uc_b3’  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     json.[0m[1;92mc:270:42[0m[39m: error: unused variable ‘uc_b4’  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The surrounding declarations at the top of the function—where `json_uchar [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39muchar;` and `unsigned char uc_b1…uc_b4;` are defined—should be reconciled with the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnew logic or removed if obsolete.  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The two-pass mechanism [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`state.first_pass`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and related buffer sizing must [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstill align with string_add and length accounting.  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Boundary checks against `end - state.ptr` should be reviewed throughout the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunction to ensure no out-of-bounds reads.  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The integration of surrogate-pair decoding into the overall parse state, [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mincluding error reporting via `[0m[1;35msprintf[0m[1;39m([0m[39merror, …[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `goto e_failed`, needs [0m       [2m                [0m
